\subtree{
  \title{4. bci.place-furnished material}

  \p{All boards, components, headers, cables, and the cap are bci.place-furnished; the assembler quotes labor only. Known shortfalls at issue date (cross-referenced as holds B1–B4 in §9) — to be verified & let Yuliya know if actually missing:}

  \table{
    \tr{\th{Area}\th{Stock / evidence}\th{Action gate}}
    \tr{\td{Sensor boards}\td{8 boards; T1M-06 ×5; C3/R1/R2 stock}\td{Need 8 J1 total (B1); probe-verify C3/R1/R2 before hand-add}}
    \tr{\td{ECU power/USB}\td{LM1085 ×2; Mini-B ×2; tactile ×3}\td{Fit-check SW1 (B2); prove U3 rail and J2 enumeration}}
    \tr{\td{ECU mux/bus}\td{T1M-10 ×8; TMUX1104 ×8; FTSH ×1}\td{Inspect mux population (B3); populate headers; map channel order}}
    \tr{\td{ST-LINK adapter}\td{5 bare boards; HTSW missing; extra FTSH needed}\td{Procure/populate adapter headers (B4) before flash path is "ready"}}
    \tr{\td{Set aside}\td{AD8618ARUZ, 1N5819W, S1SS mates, unmatched E4F}\td{Do not place without exact footprint/designator match}}
  }

  \p{No substitutions of bci.place-furnished material without written bci.place approval.}
}

\subtree{
  \title{5. Workmanship & handling standards}

  \ul{
    \li{Hand-solder acceptance to IPC-A-610 Class 2.}
    \li{ESD handling per ANSI/ESD S20.20 practice throughout.}
    \li{bci.place can provide a working station at MOX, 1618 Mission Street, San Francisco, with a fan, air filter, soldering bench, and ESD wrist straps. The assembler may use their own qualified station instead.}
    \li{First power-on of each board behind a current limit; no rework on powered boards.}
    \li{Defective or damaged CFM: stop work on that item, photograph, report per §9 non-conformance. Do not rework existing factory SMT population without written go-ahead.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{6. Work items}

  \p{Each work item lists assembly tasks and acceptance evidence. Acceptance artifacts are deliverables and feed the WI-9 evidence bundle. Quote each WI as a separate line in §7 quotation table.}
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-1 — Inventory & kitting — qty 1 kit}

  \ul{
    \li{Count and map against the kit: 8 sensor boards, 1 ECU, 5 adapter boards, all headers, muxes, USB connector, regulator, switch.}
    \li{Produce a population map recording each board's as-received condition (§3). Missing/unpopulated positions are tracked as assembly conditions, not footnotes.}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: population map + shortfall list, signed.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-2 — Sensor module hand-assembly — qty 8 boards}

  \ul{
    \li{Hand-solder per board: J1 (Samtec T1M-06-F-SH-L-K, bottom-edge 6-pad).}
    \li{Probe-verify R1 / R2 / C1 / C2 / C3 / D1 / D2 before hand-add. R1 and R2 are the only planned passive backups; C3 is shown as placed in the May 27 checklist but still gets value verification.}
    \li{Do not place AD8618ARUZ at U1. Current canonical source says sensor U1 is AD8616 SOIC-8 and is already placed by JLC; AD8618ARUZ is set-aside spare stock.}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: per-board dark/light analog response log + photo.}
    \li{⚠ Hold B1: only 5 of 8 J1 connectors stocked — completion capped at 5 boards until parts arrive.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-3 — ECU assembly & power-up — qty 1}

  \p{Ordered steps: 1. Footprint fit-check SW1 (hold B2). 2. Fit U3 (LM1085), J2 (USB Mini-B), SW1. 3. Prove the 3.3 V rail and J2 USB enumeration before further population. 4. Place 8× T1M-10 headers. 5. Inspect TMUX1104 ×8 population (hold B3). 6. Map mux select lines to channel order.}

  \ul{
    \li{Acceptance evidence: rail measurement, USB enumeration evidence, mux truth table + ADC response per channel.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-4 — ST-LINK adapter population — qty 5}

  \ul{
    \li{Boards arrive bare. Populate HTSW J1 and second FTSH J2 headers.}
    \li{⚠ Hold B4: HTSW missing, extra FTSH needed — flash path is not "ready" until procured.}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: 5 populated adapters, continuity-checked.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-5 — Firmware flash — qty 1}

  \ul{
    \li{Flash STM32L476 via SWD through the ST-LINK adapter (ECU J3 = reserved FTSH). bci.place supplies firmware image + expected hash.}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: flash log with hash readback; fresh flash with no improvised wiring.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-6 — Emitter & detector bring-up — qty 1 unit}

  \ul{
    \li{STM32 timers / GPIO expander sequence 660/940 nm LEDs on the selected module; photodiode/TIA returns analog through the connector to the ECU ADC (DMA).}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: LED current/optical within bound; non-saturated ADC samples.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-7 — USB CDC framing — qty 1 unit}

  \ul{
    \li{Frame channel, wavelength, timing, and ADC values to the host.}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: serial frame log. Frame contract must match the channel/wavelength/cap map.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-8 — Cap & cable integration + safety — qty 1 unit}

  \ul{
    \li{Cable mates, strain relief, optode spacing (35 mm source–detector), skin-contact surfaces, shielding, USB isolation.}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: completed safety checklist. Bench-safe ≠ body-safe — no human subject in this scope.}
  }
}

\subtree{
  \title{WI-9 — Release QA / evidence bundle — qty 1}

  \ul{
    \li{Compile: 8 sensor photos, ECU photo, adapter photo, BOM counts, firmware hash, channel map, and rail/optical/USB/host evidence.}
    \li{Acceptance evidence: evidence bundle delivered for bci.place review.}
  }
}

